                    <heading>Social Welfare</heading>
                    <p>In May 2019 the Government confirmed an increase in the minimum wage to a level equivalent to 43% of the average salary, with effect from 1 July, to be followed by a reduction in the health insurance contribution paid by employers, from a rate of 4.3% to 2.3%.</p>
                    <p>In response to the COVID-19 pandemic, in April 2020 the Government announced wide-ranging financial support measures to soften the economic impact on businesses and workers. In addition, the European Union provided immediate support amounting to some €3m. for the country’s health sector, and allocated funds of up to €50m. under its pre-accession instrument to aid Montenegro’s social and economic recovery.</p>
